cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.SE

This paper proposes an improvement for reachability analysis techniques for hybrid systems, which are typically studied in the subfield of control theory (cs.SY). The proposed algorithm involves dividing the search space into sub-spaces, which could also be relevant to the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of iterative successor computations suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), while the focus on scalability and efficiency could also be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
